    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="398"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_LB1">Breckinridge Long</persName> Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1" type="from">Colonel E. M. House</persName> to
                        the Third Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LB1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-15">15 December,
                            1918</date>.<lb/>[Received January 7, 1919.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. <persName corresp="#p_LB1">Long</persName>
                    </hi>: I thank you for your letter of the 26th ultimo, enclosing a copy of a
                    memorandum on International Telegraphic Communication, which you handed to Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">Lansing</persName>.<note n="1" xml:id="d398fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> I shall read this memorandum with great interest, as the subject is one
                    I am very much concerned about, and I trust that something can be worked out at
                    the Conference along the lines that you have indicated.</p>
                <p>With very best wishes, I am,</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">E. M. House</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
